{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775834873177,"sessionID":"ses_2880187b1ffeUWngSS3Bdj3DMX","part":{"id":"prt_d77fe873a001HNDgNWlUoZN40y","messageID":"msg_d77fe792d001IISTNh7z57nzou","sessionID":"ses_2880187b1ffeUWngSS3Bdj3DMX","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_9256932b25044687ba9c7267","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. The overall project structure (top-level directories and key files)\n2. What exists in pkg/store/ currently - read all files there\n3. Any existing Redis-related code or configuration anywhere in the project\n4. Any design documents, specs, or AR (Architecture Request) documents related to AR-013 or ST-3\n5. The store interface/contract that any Redis implementation would need to satisfy\n6. Any existing store implementations (e.g., in-memory, other backends) to understand patterns\n7. Go module dependencies (go.mod) to see what Redis client libraries are available\n8. Any test patterns used in the project\n\nSearch broadly - look for files matching patterns like:\n- **/AR-013*\n- **/ST-3*\n- **/store/**\n- **/*redis*\n- **/*design*\n- **/*spec*\n- **/*.md (for any documentation)\n\nReturn ALL findings in detail - file paths, contents, and structure. This is critical for writing an accurate tasks.md checklist.","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_2880163d0ffezOEXk6lw4xXtEP (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a complete picture of the project. Here is the comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n## COMPLETE AGENTCUBE PROJECT EXPLORATION REPORT\n\n### 1. OVERALL PROJECT STRUCTURE\n\n**Top-level directories and key files:**\n\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/\n├── .sdd_prompt.md                    # SDD prompt for AR-013 design generation\n├── changes/                          # AR (Architecture Request) change folders\n│   ├── AR-001/ through AR-013/       # Each has design.md, proposal.md, tasks.md, sometimes delta-spec.md\n├── ci-cd/                            # CI/CD design.md, spec.md\n├── cli-toolkit/                      # CLI toolkit design.md, spec.md\n├── client-go/                        # Generated K8s client code\n├── code-execution/                   # Code execution design.md, spec.md\n├── coverage.out                      # Test coverage output\n├── delta-spec.md                     # AR-013 Delta Spec (Gherkin-style requirements)\n├── deployment/                       # Deployment design.md, spec.md, client-go.md\n├── design.md                         # AR-012 Session Store Interface Definition -- Design\n├── go.mod                            # Go module definition\n├── go.sum                            # Go dependency checksums\n├── idle-cleanup/                     # Idle cleanup design.md, spec.md\n├── integrations/                     # Integrations design.md, spec.md\n├── pkg/                              # Main Go source packages\n│   ├── apis/runtime/v1alpha1/        # CRD type definitions\n│   ├── common/types/                 # Shared type aliases\n│   ├── router/                       # HTTP router + session manager\n│   ├── store/                        # Session storage (Redis/Valkey)\n│   └── workloadmanager/              # Workload manager (handler, reconciler, response)\n├── project.md                        # Project context overview\n├── proposal.md                       # AR-011 Router JWT auth proposal\n├── python-sdk/                       # Python SDK design.md, spec.md\n├── sandbox-orchestration/            # Sandbox orchestration design.md, spec.md\n├── session-routing/                  # Session routing design.md, spec.md\n├── session-store/                    # Session store spec.md, design.md\n├── test_spec.md                      # TDD test case specification\n└── testing/                          # TDD manifest\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. pkg/store/ -- ALL FILES (9 files total)\n\n| File | Absolute Path | Lines | Purpose |\n|------|--------------|-------|---------|\n| `store.go` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store.go` | 35 | `Store` interface definition + `ErrNotFound` + `Storage()` accessor |\n| `singleton.go` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/singleton.go` | 31 | `sync.Once` singleton, provider selection via `STORE_TYPE` env var |\n| `store_redis.go` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store_redis.go` | 235 | Redis implementation (`redisStore` struct) |\n| `store_redis_test.go` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store_redis_test.go` | 439 | Redis unit tests (miniredis-based) |\n| `store_valkey.go` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | 246 | Valkey implementation (`valkeyStore` struct) |\n| `store_valkey_test.go` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store_valkey_test.go` | 241 | Valkey unit tests |\n| `codec.go` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/codec.go` | 19 | JSON encode/decode helpers |\n| `codec_test.go` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/codec_test.go` | 111 | Codec unit tests |\n| `singleton_test.go` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/singleton_test.go` | 85 | Singleton/provider selection tests |\n\n---\n\n### 3. REDIS-RELATED CODE AND CONFIGURATION\n\n**Existing Redis files:**\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store_redis.go` -- Full Redis store implementation\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/store/store_redis_test.go` -- Full test suite\n\n**Redis client dependency (from go.mod):**\n- `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9 v9.18.0` -- Direct dependency\n- `github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2 v2.37.0` -- In-memory Redis for testing\n\n**Redis usage in other packages:**\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/server.go` -- Calls `store.Storage()` to get store client\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/session_manager.go` -- Wraps `store.Store` in `SessionManager`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/agentruntime.go` -- Calls `r.store.StoreSandbox()`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/codeinterpreter.go` -- Calls `r.store.StoreSandbox()`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_create.go` -- Defines its own `Store` interface (different signature!)\n\n**Environment variables for Redis:**\n- `REDIS_ADDR` (required)\n- `REDIS_PASSWORD` (required unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`)\n- `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` (default: `true`)\n- `STORE_TYPE` (default: `redis`)\n\n---\n\n### 4. AR-013 DOCUMENTS (ALL 3 FILES FOUND)\n\n**Location:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-013/`\n\n| File | Absolute Path | Lines |\n|------|--------------|-------|\n| `design.md` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-013/design.md` | 707 |\n| `proposal.md` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-013/proposal.md` | 90 |\n| `tasks.md` | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-013/tasks.md` | 9 |\n\n**AR-013 tasks.md content (all unchecked):**\n```\n- [ ] 1. Define Redis store interface and types\n- [ ] 2. Implement Redis connection management\n- [ ] 3. Implement core store operations (Get, Set, Delete)\n- [ ] 4. Add serialization/deserialization helpers\n- [ ] 5. Write unit tests\n- [ ] 6. Write integration tests\n- [ ] 7. Update documentation\n```\n\n**AR-013 proposal.md key points:**\n- Module: `pkg/store`, Language: Go, Size: M\n- Identifies 6 deviations between current implementation and spec/design docs:\n  1. Interface signature mismatch (`GetSandbox` vs `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `StoreSandbox` params)\n  2. Error message mismatch (`\"sandbox not found\"` vs `\"store: not found\"`)\n  3. List methods use N+1 queries instead of Pipeline/MGET\n  4. Missing `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` helper\n  5. `limit int` vs `limit int64`\n  6. Missing `ExpiresAt` zero-value validation in `StoreSandbox`\n\n**ST-3 reference:** No files matching `**/ST-3*` were found anywhere in the project. The `test_spec.md` references `TestCase-ST-001` and `TestCase-ST-002` for store-layer tests, and the TDD manifest references `Test-ST-1` and `Test-ST-2`, but there is no ST-3 document.\n\n---\n\n### 5. STORE INTERFACE/CONTRACT\n\n**Current interface in `store.go` (what EXISTS in code):**\n\n```go\nvar ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"sandbox not found\")  // NOTE: spec says \"store: not found\"\n\ntype Store interface {\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    GetSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListSandboxes(ctx context.Context) (map[string]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n    ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n    Close() error\n}\n```\n\n**Spec/design interface (what the spec SAYS it should be):**\n\n```go\nvar ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")  // Different message!\n\ntype Store interface {\n    Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n    GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)  // Different name!\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error  // Different signature!\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error  // Different signature!\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)  // int64!\n    ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)  // int64!\n    UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n    Close() error\n}\n```\n\n**CRITICAL GAP:** The current `store.go` interface does NOT match the spec/design. The AR-013 proposal explicitly calls this out. The current code has:\n- `GetSandbox` (spec wants `GetSandboxBySessionID`)\n- `StoreSandbox(ctx, sessionID string, info *SandboxInfo)` (spec wants `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandboxStore *SandboxInfo)`)\n- `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sessionID string, info *SandboxInfo)` (spec wants `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandboxStore *SandboxInfo)`)\n- `limit int` (spec wants `limit int64`)\n- `ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"sandbox not found\")` (spec wants `\"store: not found\"`)\n- Extra method `ListSandboxes` not in spec\n\n**Additional Store interfaces in other packages (INCONSISTENT):**\n\n1. **`pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_create.go`** defines its own:\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, info *SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *SandboxInfo) error\n    GetSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*SandboxInfo, error)\n    DeleteSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    ListSandboxes(ctx context.Context) ([]*SandboxInfo, error)\n}\n```\n\n2. **`pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/types.go`** defines its own:\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *handler.SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *handler.SandboxInfo) error\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    GetSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*handler.SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListSandboxes(ctx context.Context) (map[string]*handler.SandboxInfo, error)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. EXISTING STORE IMPLEMENTATIONS\n\n**Two implementations exist: Redis and Valkey**\n\n**`redisStore` struct** (`store_redis.go`):\n```go\ntype redisStore struct {\n    cli                  redis.UniversalClient  // NOTE: spec says *redisv9.Client\n    sessionPrefix        string\n    expiryIndexKey       string\n    lastActivityIndexKey string\n}\n```\n\nKey implementation details:\n- Constructor: `newRedisStore() Store` (returns `Store`, not `(*redisStore, error)` as spec says)\n- Uses `klog.Fatal()` for init errors (spec says should return errors)\n- Uses `redis.UniversalClient` interface (spec says `*redisv9.Client`)\n- `StoreSandbox` uses pipeline: `SETNX` + `ZADD` (expiry) + `ZADD` (activity)\n- `UpdateSandbox` uses `SetXX` (SET with XX flag)\n- `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` uses pipeline: `DEL` + `ZREM` (expiry) + `ZREM` (activity)\n- `ListExpiredSandboxes` / `ListInactiveSandboxes` use **N+1 pattern** (loop GET) -- NOT the MGET/pipeline pattern the spec requires\n- No `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` helper method exists (spec requires it)\n- No `ExpiresAt.IsZero()` validation in `StoreSandbox` (spec requires it)\n\n**`valkeyStore` struct** (`store_valkey.go`):\n```go\ntype valkeyStore struct {\n    cli                  valkey.Client\n    sessionPrefix        string\n    expiryIndexKey       string\n    lastActivityIndexKey string\n}\n```\n\nSimilar pattern to Redis but uses valkey-go's type-safe command builder API. Same gaps (no MGET batch loading, no ExpiresAt validation).\n\n**`singleton.go`** -- Provider selection:\n```go\nfunc initStore() error {\n    storeType := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"STORE_TYPE\"))\n    if storeType == \"\" { storeType = \"redis\" }\n    switch storeType {\n    case \"redis\":  storeInstance = newRedisStore()\n    case \"valkey\": storeInstance = newValkeyStore()\n    default:       return fmt.Errorf(\"unsupported store type: %s\", storeType)\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n**`codec.go`** -- JSON helpers:\n```go\nfunc encodeSandboxInfo(info *types.SandboxInfo) ([]byte, error)\nfunc decodeSandboxInfo(data []byte) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. GO MODULE DEPENDENCIES (go.mod)\n\n**Module:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n**Go version:** `go 1.25.0`\n\n**Redis-related direct dependencies:**\n| Module | Version | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | `v9.18.0` | Redis client library |\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | `v1.0.73` | Valkey client library |\n| `github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2` | `v2.37.0` | In-memory Redis for testing |\n\n**Other notable dependencies:**\n| Module | Version | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/stretchr/testify` | `v1.11.1` | Test assertions (assert/require) |\n| `github.com/google/uuid` | `v1.6.0` | UUID generation |\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | `v1.10.0` | HTTP framework |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | `v2.130.1` | Structured logging |\n| `k8s.io/api` | `v0.34.1` | K8s API types |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | `v0.34.1` | K8s client |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | `v0.22.2` | K8s controller runtime |\n\n---\n\n### 8. TEST PATTERNS\n\n**Testing framework:** `github.com/stretchr/testify` (assert + require packages)\n\n**Redis test pattern** (`store_redis_test.go`):\n```go\nfunc newTestRedisStore(t *testing.T) (*redisStore, *miniredis.Miniredis) {\n    t.Helper()\n    mr, err := miniredis.Run()\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    t.Cleanup(func() { mr.Close() })\n    cli := redis.NewClient(&redis.Options{Addr: mr.Addr()})\n    t.Cleanup(func() { cli.Close() })\n    return &redisStore{cli: cli, sessionPrefix: \"session:\", ...}, mr\n}\n\nfunc testSandboxInfo(sessionID string) *types.SandboxInfo {\n    now := time.Now().UTC()\n    return &types.SandboxInfo{SessionID: sessionID, ...}\n}\n```\n\n**Test naming convention:** `Test<StructName>_<MethodName>_<Scenario>`\n- Examples: `TestRedisStore_Ping`, `TestRedisStore_GetSandbox_NotFound`, `TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_Success`, `TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox_RoundTrip`, `TestRedisStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_OrphanMember`\n\n**Valkey test pattern** (`store_valkey_test.go`):\n- Tests use direct struct initialization (no miniredis equivalent for Valkey)\n- Environment variable tests use `os.Setenv`/`os.Unsetenv` with `defer` cleanup\n- Constructor tests expect `klog.Fatal` panics via `recover()`\n\n**Singleton test pattern** (`singleton_test.go`):\n- Tests `initStore()` directly (not through `Storage()`) to avoid sync.Once issues\n- Concurrent access test uses goroutines + channels to verify same instance\n\n**Codec test pattern** (`codec_test.go`):\n- Round-trip encode/decode tests\n- Invalid JSON input tests with table-driven approach\n- Nil/empty input edge cases\n\n**TDD Manifest requirements** (`testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md`):\n- T/C Ratio must be > 0.4 (40 lines of test per 100 lines of code)\n- Every source file must have corresponding `*_test.go`\n\n**Gate requirements** (from design docs):\n1. `go build ./pkg/store/...` compiles\n2. `go test ./pkg/store/... -v` all pass\n3. `go test -race ./pkg/store/...` no data race warnings\n4. No `log.Printf` usage (use klog)\n5. No sensitive data in logs\n6. Test coverage >= 80% for `store_redis.go`\n\n---\n\n### 9. KEY DATA TYPE: SandboxInfo\n\n**Actual definition** (`pkg/workloadmanager/handler/models.go`):\n```go\ntype SandboxInfo struct {\n    SessionID      string       `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    SandboxName    string       `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n    SandboxID      string       `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    WorkloadName   string       `json:\"workloadName\"`\n    Namespace      string       `json:\"namespace\"`\n    Kind           string       `json:\"kind\"`\n    PodIP          string       `json:\"podIp,omitempty\"`\n    EntryPoints    []EntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints,omitempty\"`\n    CreatedAt      time.Time    `json:\"createdAt\"`\n    ExpiresAt      time.Time    `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n    Status         string       `json:\"status\"`\n    LastActivityAt time.Time    `json:\"lastActivityAt\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Type alias** (`pkg/common/types/types.go`):\n```go\ntype SandboxInfo = handler.SandboxInfo\ntype EntryPoint = handler.EntryPoint\n```\n\n---\n\n### 10. CRITICAL GAPS IDENTIFIED (for tasks.md)\n\n1. **Interface mismatch**: `store.go` interface does not match spec/design (method names, signatures, `limit` type, `ErrNotFound` message)\n2. **Missing `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs`**: Both Redis and Valkey implementations use N+1 GET loops instead of batch MGET/pipeline\n3. **Missing `ExpiresAt.IsZero()` validation**: `StoreSandbox` does not reject zero expiry times\n4. **Constructor returns `Store` not `(*redisStore, error)`**: Current `newRedisStore()` calls `klog.Fatal()` instead of returning errors\n5. **Client type mismatch**: Uses `redis.UniversalClient` instead of `*redisv9.Client` as spec requires\n6. **No `sessionKey()` helper method**: Key construction is inlined (`r.sessionPrefix + sessionID`)\n7. **Three different `Store` interfaces** exist across `pkg/store`, `pkg/workloadmanager/handler`, and `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler` -- all with different signatures\n8. **No `ListSandboxes` in spec** but it exists in the current interface\n9. **tasks.md is entirely unchecked** -- all 7 tasks are still `[ ]`\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_2880163d0ffezOEXk6lw4xXtEP","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project","time":{"start":1775834668077,"end":1775834873174}}}}
